\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line Background\line ATTI \'28Advanced Technology Training Institute\'29 Nelspruit is a new private higher education institution. It does not have any programmes that are accredited by the HEQC and is not registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a private higher education provider. \line \line The Diploma in Information Technology  programme served in the AC Meeting of 23 February 2011 and the HEQC decided not to accredit it for the following reasons\'3A\line \line 1. Although an outline of the curriculum has been provided\'2C the institution has not included the programme learning outcomes. Competencies expected of students on completion need to be made explicit and should be in keeping with the level of the programme. Given insufficient information\'2C it is not clear that the requisite level of provision is being proposed. \line \line 2. The programme appears to be dominated by the teaching of practical skills in application software\'2C programming software and networking without sufficient theoretical rigour underpinning the programme. \line \line 3. Copies of advertising material are not in keeping with the HE band in terms of DHET and SAQA regulations. \line \line 4. The admission requirements for the programme do not adhere to current legislation for HE in terms the National Senior Certificate. Selection tests should not be regarded as part of the admission requirements but rather used for selection purposes. \line \line 5. Selection criteria for entry in to the programme are not explicit and are confused with minimum admission requirements. \line \line 6. Some staff members identified for the programme do not have the required minimum qualification of a degree. \line \line 7. The majority of the staff members identified for the programme do not have teaching experience in a recognized higher education institution. \line \line 8. Staff members do not have sufficient experience of assessment in higher education. \line \line 9. There is a lack of clarity regarding the different assessment methods and their relative weights such that the appropriateness cannot be determined. \line \line 10. The institution has made provision for external moderation of assessment. However\'2C there is a lack of specificity regarding the process by which external moderators are appointed\'2C as well as their roles and responsibilities. \line \line 11. A description of the books in the library indicates that they are suitable mainly for the development of practical skills. The institution has not provided adequate resources to promote the link between theory and practice. These include mostly operating manuals from Microsoft \'28A\'2B\'2C MSCE\'2C MSCD\'2C Java\'29 a more comprehensive provisioning of appropriate resources is required. \line \cell \pard 

