\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\cellx9639

\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The institution has submitted additional evidence as part of their representation. The evaluator of the representation indicated that most of the reasons listed for not accrediting the programme have been addressed\'2C with the exception of concerns related to staffing. \line \line In terms of programme design\'2C the evaluator stated that a complete list of learning outcomes and competences expected of the students after completion of this programme has been provided. It is an acceptable reflection of learning outcomes for an IT programme and the competences are at appropriate levels for this Diploma in IT. The evaluator also noted that the institution has capabilities for providing practical training programmes while they are trying to serve the community by introducing a HE programme which needs both theoretical and practical training. It is in the interest of the students and the community in general\'2C in that part of SA\'2C to have access to a choice of programmes that are multi-faceted. The evidence presented in the representation indicates that they will meet this challenge. ATTI\'2C in their representation submissions\'2C has identified and pointed out the theoretical components \'28contents\'29 in each of the modules for this programme. The evaluator considered this as clear evidence that ATTI can present this programme at the appropriate level which will have the necessary theoretical and practical contents.\line \line The admission requirements have been amended. It is stated as a National Senior Certificate which is appropriate for this programme.  A paper-based selection test and an interview form part of the selection process. Those candidates who meet the minimum requirements for admission will go through this selection process prior to admission. This process is used for career guidance and to ensure that the candidate has the aptitude for this programme.\line \line Assessment components\'2C formative and summative\'2C and their weights have been clearly specified for the modules in the programme\'3B 10\'25 for formative \'28course work\'29 and 90\'25 for the summative part. The evaluator recommended that the ratio for formative component be increased to 40\'25 by including class tests and tutorial assignments.  the Moderation Policy document states clearly the steps for internal moderation and external moderation processes. It also states the procedure for the appointment of internal and external moderators. The roles and responsibilities of the internal and external moderation processes have been elaborated.\line \line In terms of concerns regarding library resources\'2C a list of titles in the library shows additional titles have been added that meet the requirements of this programme.\line \line As stated the only outstanding concerns relates to staffing. One staff member has the required level of training\'2C but with no HE teaching experience. No staff member at the institution has teaching experience in a recognized higher education institution. Assessment experience at HE level is also lacking for staff members.\line \line The Directorate supports the recommendation that the programme should be accredited with conditions.\line \cell \pard 

